headline: Intel Slashes Arrow Lake Prices Amid Tough Competition From AMD
summary: Intel officially cut the suggested retail price of its 265K Arrow Lake desktop CPU.  The move makes the mid-range chip more competitive, although gaming performance remains an issue.  This could be a sign that Intel is getting more aggressive on pricing as it tries to regain market share.
